<br>
&quot;Ya kinna change the laws of physics!&quot;<br>
<br>
I don't know where he got THAT idea.  First we can't dual wield, then we can.  We used to be able to hold aggro and now we can't.  Other monsters used to just hate us, and now they hardly even look our way.  We can strike our enemies faster than even before (ALL HAIL CYRICUS THE LIBERATOR!).<br>
<br>
It is was so simple before.  The right element for the right job.  No longer.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, borrowing all those super resist raid buffs and all the gear resists can be actually quite cool when it works out like it's supposed to.<br>
<br>
One last thing.  Now I'm pushing my Non-Elemental Disclosure Agreement here a bit, but my advice is to figure out how this resist thing works and get it all fixed up as soon as you can.  See, in the new planes, we elementals are going to take a lot of damage.  Now for the right element we should be mostly immune, and sometimes we are, but sometimes we aren't when the resists are screwy, and that's when we die and die quickly.<br>
<br>
And we all know what short lived elementals leads to, don't we?<br>
<br>
Chain casting pets.<br>
<br>
Well!<br>
<br>
I think I've said enough, I'm beginning to see a portal open up....<br>
